(42, 18, 29, 5, 33, 9, 9, 'for the kingdom of God’s sake', 'Sacrifice for God''s Kingdom', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of prioritizing commitment to God over familial ties. Luke 18:29 speaks of leaving family for the kingdom of God, while Deuteronomy 33:9 highlights a similar disregard for familial recognition in favor of observing God''s word.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 30, 18, 42, 10, 10, 'manifold more in this present time', 'Restoration and Abundance', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of receiving more than before after enduring trials. Job''s restoration of ''twice as much'' parallels the promise of ''manifold more'' in Luke, highlighting divine reward in both contexts.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 30, 58, 13, 5, 6, NULL, 'Contentment and Divine Assurance', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of contentment and trust in God''s provision. Luke 18:30 speaks of receiving manifold blessings, while Hebrews 13:5-6 encourages believers to be content, assuring them of God''s constant presence.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 30, 66, 2, 17, 17, 'life everlasting', 'Eternal Rewards Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the promise of rewards for believers. Luke 18:30 speaks of receiving ''life everlasting,'' while Revelation 2:17 mentions rewards for ''him that overcometh,'' including hidden manna and a new name.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 30, 40, 12, 32, 32, 'in the world to come', 'Forgiveness and Life Everlasting', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of actions in this world and the world to come. Luke 18:30 speaks of receiving life everlasting, while Matthew 12:32 discusses forgiveness in relation to the Holy Ghost, highlighting the significance of one''s choices in both realms.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 30, 42, 12, 31, 32, 'manifold more in this present time', 'Seeking the Kingdom''s Rewards', 'Both passages emphasize the rewards of seeking God''s kingdom. Luke 18:30 mentions receiving manifold more in this present time, while Luke 12:31-32 assures that seeking the kingdom will lead to additional blessings.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
