(42, 18, 31, 19, 22, 1, 31, NULL, 'Connection of Suffering and Deliverance', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of suffering and the cry for help. In Luke, the reference to the fulfillment of prophecies connects to the deep anguish expressed in Psalms 22, particularly the plea for divine assistance amidst distress.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 31, 41, 10, 32, 34, 'we go up to Jerusalem', 'Journey to Jerusalem and Prophecy', 'Both passages emphasize the journey to Jerusalem and the fulfillment of prophetic events concerning the Son of man. They highlight the impending suffering and death that Jesus will face, as well as his resurrection on the third day.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 31, 40, 16, 21, 21, 'we go up to Jerusalem', 'Journey to Jerusalem and Suffering', 'Both passages emphasize the journey to Jerusalem and the suffering that Jesus will endure. Luke highlights the fulfillment of prophetic writings, while Matthew details the specific sufferings Jesus will face there.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 31, 38, 13, 7, 7, 'all things that are written by the prophets', 'Connection of Shepherd and Suffering', 'This connection highlights the theme of the shepherd''s suffering, as indicated in both passages. Luke 18:31 refers to the fulfillment of prophetic writings concerning the Son of man, while Zechariah 13:7 speaks of the shepherd being smitten, leading to the scattering of the sheep.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 31, 42, 9, 22, 22, 'all things that are written by the prophets', 'Connection of Suffering and Prophecy', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of suffering for the Son of man. Luke 18:31 indicates that all things written by the prophets will be accomplished, including the suffering mentioned in Luke 9:22.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 32, 42, 23, 11, 11, 'shall be mocked', 'Mocking of Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the mocking of Jesus during his trial. In Luke 18:32, it is foretold that he will be mocked, and in Luke 23:11, Herod and his men mock him, fulfilling this prophecy.', 'prophecy', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 32, 23, 50, 6, 6, NULL, 'Connection of Suffering and Mocking', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of suffering and humiliation faced by the servant. Luke 18:32 mentions being ''mocked'' and ''spitted on,'' while Isaiah 50:6 describes giving ''my back to the smiters'' and not hiding from ''shame and spitting.''', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
